Class NumberTile

  • java.lang.Object
    • NumberTile

  • public class NumberTile
extends java.lang.Object

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      NumberTile()
      NumberTile constructor creates an Integer ArrayList and adds 4 random integers in the range of 1 to 9 to the ArrayList.

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getLeft()
      getLeft is an Accessor method that returns the value in the left position of the tile (index 0).

      getRight is an Accessor method that returns the value in the right position of the tile (index 2).

      rotate method removes the last object in the ArrayList and puts it in the first location.

    • Constructor Detail

      • NumberTile

        public NumberTile()
        NumberTile constructor creates an Integer ArrayList and adds 4 random integers in the range of 1 to 9 to the ArrayList.

    • Method Detail

      • rotate

        public void rotate()
        rotate method removes the last object in the ArrayList and puts it in the first location. This moves all objects back 1 position, effectively rotating the tile 90 degrees.

      • getLeft

        public int getLeft()
        getLeft is an Accessor method that returns the value in the left position of the tile (index 0).
        Returns:
        index 0, value at left location of tile.

      • getRight

        public int getRight()
        getRight is an Accessor method that returns the value in the right position of the tile (index 2).
        Returns:
        index 2, value at right location of tile.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        toString overrides the ArrayList method and returns a formated string that can be sent to console. This displays an individual tile in console. returns the tile as a string in the form : 4 5 7 1
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        returns a formated string object that can be used to display a tile
